    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Scrolling control is an awful mess, full of edge-cases. I'm not quite sure how easy this one is to fix, b/c I know people have wrestled already pretty hard with the scrolling code and it tends to turn into a game of whack-a-mole.   What we need is a test harness that can check those things, so we can gradually build an increasingly tight set of tests around such behavior.  Otherwise we'll fix one thing, only to discover weeks later that it makes some other scroll-related behavior worse...\n"
  },
